				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any tips for two boxing<a name="18026"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 12:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Depends on the level, any damage dealer and healer can do pretty good.
<br />

<br />
Look at the old ez-boards....this is a good discussion of two boxiing at the end game.
<br />

<br />
http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm1.showMessage?topicID=11175.topic
<br />

<br />
Sorry, I haven't figured out how to make links here.
<br />

<br />
Bard/healer is about the same as any melee through twenty.
<br />

<br />
Post 20, mana regen of the bard is handy, but ability to tank vs pally/warrior/ranger etc with a healing partner falls off mid 40's or so. 
<br />

<br />
The bard can compensate some with his ability to charm a helper, for instance, or boosting dps with chants. He can alsoy slow a bit, which helps the healer.
<br />

<br />
I bot warrior/cleric, ranger/cleric, bard/cleric, pally/cleric and beastlord/necro.
<br />

<br />
When one or both classes are more difficult to run (pet class, bard, it gets a little hairy.)
<br />

<br />
Bard can chant kite circles around druid/cleric/nuker in kind of an aggro kite. Its fun.  Druid would add more here.
<br />

<br />
If you can truly run two tunes at a time, you can use the second box to finish off low heathl in your swarming. I have done it, but its tuff.
<br />

<br />
You pretty much can not use a second box to heal a bard during a swarm.  Aggro will transfer.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Thats just a small tast, go to the druid/cleric boards and post the same two box question to get a different take. (Clerics tend to view warriors as their own personal pets, lol).
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
