				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any tips for two boxing<a name="18087"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><a target="_new" href="http://www.eqwindows.com/">EQW</a>
<br />

<br />
is your friend.  their site seems to be down atm, but its a great program that i use all the time to 2box.
<br />

<br />
i have 2boxed a few odd combos:
<br />

<br />
bard/wiz
<br />
nec/wiz
<br />
sk/cleric
<br />

<br />
are the 3 i have the most with in group, but have used my nec to PL the wiz, sk before too.
<br />

<br />
few things about 2boxing if you are not running 2 computers:
<br />

<br />
1.  more ram is nice
<br />
2.  better vid card you can get the better results you will have and less lag
<br />
3.  one account should have everything off (particle effects, sound, 3d sky, etc)
<br />
4.  turn sound off on both accounts
<br />

<br />
good luck.  enjoy and have fun.  
<br />

<br />
with a 2.4G P4 800Mhz FSB, 1G pc3200, ATI 9500 128M vid card i can 2box even in PoK with limited lag.
<br />

<br />
i do run with 3d sky on, no sound, all effects off on both accounts.  if im in a zone with less lag (not many ppl, or not realy heavy on the graphics) ill crank up my mp3 player in game and still have no issues, but in places like PoK, or baz, or some of the LDoN camps i have to turn off the Mp3 player.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
