			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any tips for two boxing<a name="18090"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 3:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll give you a couple of for instance'es:
<br />

<br />
I have a 52 bard/51 cleric duo sitting in KC as I write this. At this level with these mobs, and a relatively well equipped 52, just strait tanking a db Karnor's mob is fairly slow. I am twisting a chant/haste/slow/mana with BDMG and Trouby.
<br />

<br />
It takes one 1/2 or 2 cheals a fight on some mobs.
<br />

<br />
If I charm a helper and the cleric melees from his horse, I only need a cheal every second round. I can typically deal with three mobs in close combat, I can root/mez/charm and ecscape from more, but I can't effectively deal with more than three without aggro transferring to the cleric, or just standing there keeping a bunch mezzed. Drop one or two songs, and either there is low dps or an unslowed mob is kicking my butt, and the cleric has to be too careful.
<br />

<br />
I have a 65 bard with only modest gear. I don't think my 52 cleric could keep him alive against a planar mob without resorting to all the things people resort to to solo bards in the plains. (Thats about 4100 hp virute buffed/1250ish ac and
<br />
1280 attack, with werewolf illusion.) Forget dealing with an add.
<br />

<br />
Of course, there are 65's out there with 4-5kish unbuffed and 1400 plus ac and that really lightens the load on a cleric.
<br />

<br />
Earlier, my bard/cleric in their mid thirties tore up crystal caverns....I would just cast down the well and let the train come to me. These are waves of 4-8 db's.
<br />

<br />
Low levels, like pre-40...the new warrior taunt/provoke and the shield command make duoing warrior/cleric a breeze. The warrior can effectively hold aggro on say, a db, even, and yelo con. (provoke one, taunt another, fight the third) enough to give the cleric a little freedom in what he casts.
<br />

<br />
Low level cleric nukes/stuns (up to mid 40's) are actully pretty efficient.
<br />

<br />
The pet class folks have an argument, as you can tell by the old diva ez board thread.
<br />

<br />
I would say, if you have never played a bard, choosing one as part of a two box plan might severely limit his development in some areas.
<br />

<br />
My ranger/cleric duo is 52. They eat through even/db cons where there is a room to manuever. Clerics are decent at crowd control if the left hand knows what the right is doing, lol. The ranger is quite adept at creating huge amounts of aggro....what this duo misses is a slow, although the ranger has a proc'ing slow weapon, its not reliable.
<br />

<br />
Its actually more mana efficient for me to nuke/stun/nuke/stun with the cleric than try and keep up the cheals on the ranger.  Once I try and do non cleric stunable mobs (55 and over), it will be time for the ranger to back off and use the artillery. At that point, I'll be wishing for more DPS from my second box than I think the cleric can supply.
<br />

<br />
Shammie would be a good partner, healing/slowing/buffing/pet.
<br />

<br />
If bards could affect pets (I am talking as they rise up from 1-60....not in some hard won AA on a future expansion). I would really be a boon for bard/pet class.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
