				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any tips for two boxing<a name="19141"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 4 04 6:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Biggest thing for multi boxing is setting up your hot keys and computers so that you are comfortable.  I 4-box a 65 war/65 ench/62 cleric/62 druid alot.  If you are multi boxing you will need to practice.  Moving around a lot will cause problems especially at first.  Also consider that you will have to have your casters medding.  If you can afford it, get them horses early.  Watching mana and hps can be an issue.  Also set up your display so you can read the message (xx is casting) or xx has been snared/healed etc.  It saves alot if you only have to look at one monitor w/o swapping or moving around.  
<br />

<br />
Also, if you swap between the cleric and druid for your multiboxing experience, ensure that their similar hot keys are the same so you don't make mistakes.  I standardized on all my secondaries (cleric/druid/ench) as many hot keys.  That way, if i do forget who is on what computer, it does not matter.  And above all Practice, Practice, Practice.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
